task.summary: Default task
More work on the LMNL grammar, wrestled with the Lexer to get more information about the tokens (Type and Mode) out of it.

More work on the LMNL Lexer grammar, it can now tokenize the whole example correctly. There is a lot of duplication between the definition of a range and an annotation, which probably can be removed in the lexicon, and the differences can be dealt with on the parser level.
Started work on creating a LMNL parser using ANTLR and the lexicon created yesterday.
Lexer: Fixed a bug in the lexer, made TestTheLMNLLexer a real unit test.
LMNL Parser: added support for parsing a single range on text. Made the TestTheLMNLParser class a real unit test.
LMNL Parser: allow an annotation to be placed on a range.
Started a simple data model. Moved all the ANTLR related files into a separate directory. Started a simple LMNL importer and visitor.
Renamed LMNLGrammar.g4 to LMNLLexer.g4
Failed attempt to simplify the lexicon and lexer.
LMNL Lexer: cleaned up the token names. LMNL Parser: added extra rules to structure grammar better.
Changed the directory structure to make it more Maven standards complaint.
Mavenized the project. Disabled the LMNL parser for the moment. I am thinking of using only the lexer for the moment.
Added textual content to Annotation class. Moved the tree based ANTLR parser to a folder called "disregarded experiments".
Added the Limen class as a container class for textual nodes.
Moved the storage of text ranges to the Limen in the LOM. Made TextRange contain the effected TextNodes.
Added TextNode -> TextRange mapping in the Limen container class. Added Limen as owner to the TextRange class.
Document: added getter for Limen. LMNLImporter: removed old remarked code and added TODO. Made LMNLImporterTest compile with the newer LOM api.
[NLA-347] extract handleAnnotation
[NLA-347] Import 1kings12, ozymandias-voices-wap, add LMNLExporter
